### Enable Screen Reader Support in Ink render function

Source: https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink/blob/master/readme.md

Pass the `isScreenReaderEnabled` option to the render function or set the `INK_SCREEN_READER` environment variable to enable screen reader support. This allows Ink to generate screen-reader-friendly output for CLI applications.

```jsx
render(<MyApp />, {isScreenReaderEnabled: true});
```

--------------------------------

### Access stdout stream using useStdout hook

Source: https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink/blob/master/readme.md

The useStdout hook exposes the stdout stream where Ink renders the application. Returns the stream passed to render() options or process.stdout by default. Useful for accessing the output stream properties.

```javascript
import {useStdout} from 'ink';

const Example = () => {
	const {stdout} = useStdout();

	return …
};
```

--------------------------------

### Ink Core Rendering with render()

Source: https://context7.com/vadimdemedes/ink/llms.txt

The main entry point for Ink applications, `render()`, mounts a React component tree to stdout. It returns an instance handle for controlling the application lifecycle and supports various configurations for streams, console patching, screen readers, and performance. The example shows basic rendering, custom configuration, and lifecycle control like `waitUntilExit()` and `unmount()`.

```javascript
import React, {useState, useEffect} from 'react';
import {render, Text, Box} from 'ink';

function App() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  useEffect(() => {
    const timer = setInterval(() => {
      setCount(c => c + 1);
    }, 1000);
    return () => clearInterval(timer);
  }, []);

  return (
    <Box flexDirection="column" padding={1}>
      <Text color="green">Counter: {count}</Text>
      <Text dimColor>Press Ctrl+C to exit</Text>
    </Box>
  );
}

// Basic rendering
const instance = render(<App />);

// Custom configuration
const customInstance = render(<App />, {
  stdout: process.stdout,
  stdin: process.stdin,
  stderr: process.stderr,
  exitOnCtrlC: true,
  patchConsole: true,
  debug: false,
  maxFps: 30,
  isScreenReaderEnabled: false
});

// Control lifecycle
await customInstance.waitUntilExit();
customInstance.unmount();
customInstance.clear();
```

--------------------------------

### Render React Component to Terminal with render()

Source: https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink/blob/master/readme.md

Core API for mounting and rendering a React component to the terminal. Accepts a ReactElement tree and optional configuration object. Returns an Instance object for managing the rendered app. Supports custom stdout, stdin, stderr streams and Ctrl+C handling.

```javascript
import {render} from 'ink';

// Basic usage
render(<App />);

// With options
render(<App />, {
	stdout: process.stdout,
	stdin: process.stdin,
	stderr: process.stderr,
	exitOnCtrlC: true
});
```

--------------------------------

### Static Component: Rendering Dynamic Lists (Ink/React)

Source: https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink/blob/master/readme.md

Demonstrates the usage of the Static component in Ink for rendering content that doesn't change after initial rendering, such as logs or completed tasks. It takes an 'items' prop, which is an array, and renders its children for each item. Changes to existing items in the 'items' array are not re-rendered, only new items trigger rendering.

```jsx
import React, {useState, useEffect} from 'react';
import {render, Static, Box, Text} from 'ink';

const Example = () => {
	const [tests, setTests] = useState([]);

	useEffect(() => {
		let completedTests = 0;
		let timer;

		const run = () => {
			// Fake 10 completed tests
			if (completedTests++ < 10) {
				setTests(previousTests => [
					...previousTests,
					{
						id: previousTests.length,
						title: `Test #${previousTests.length + 1}`
					}
				]);

				timer = setTimeout(run, 100);
			}
		};

		run();

		return () => {
			clearTimeout(timer);
		};
	}, []);

	return (
		<>
			{/* This part will be rendered once to the terminal */}
			<Static items={tests}>
				{test => (
					<Box key={test.id}>
						<Text color="green">✔ {test.title}</Text>
					</Box>
				)}
			</Static>

			{/* This part keeps updating as state changes */}
			<Box marginTop={1}>
				<Text dimColor>Completed tests: {tests.length}</Text>
			</Box>
		</>
	);
};

render(<Example />);
```

```jsx
<Static items={...} style={{padding: 1}}>
	{...}
</Static>
```

