### Check raw mode support and conditionally render in Ink

Source: https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink/blob/master/readme.md

Uses useStdin's isRawModeSupported flag to detect if the current stdin supports raw mode, allowing components to gracefully fall back to alternative rendering when raw mode is unavailable. This prevents errors in environments without TTY support.

```javascript
import {useStdin} from 'ink';

const Example = () => {
	const {isRawModeSupported} = useStdin();

	return isRawModeSupported ? (
		<MyInputComponent />
	) : (
		<MyComponentThatDoesntUseInput />
	);
};
```

